      "subcategory": "Notes",
      "activityName": "Notes on Mixing Concrete",
      "description": "This data provides information needed to compute the time required to survey a parcel or to perform the layout for a construction project. Hand mixing using two boards eliminates waiting for a batch to be mixed before dry charging the mixing board, as the mixers alternate boards. With twelve men, the maximum output is about 8 CYD per day. Warm weather (90 to 100 degrees) will slow mixing time and add 0.5 man-hours per CYD. Labor to charge a mixer can be reduced by the use of a small front-end loader, but at least one man must remain on each aggregate stock pile to monitor bucket loading. Transit mix man-hours are based on using four trucks, average haul of five miles, and four men operating a dry cement batching plant. Large job man-day estimates are dependent on equipment used, as well as manufacturer\u2019s ratings and recommendations.",
